        <h1>Help us to translate Phylo!</h1>
        <p>
        Conserving the language diversity is important.
        We wish to distribute <a href="http://phylo.cs.mcgill.ca">Phylo</a> in as many languages as possible.
        To reach this goal, we need your help! This page contains all the material and instructions you need to
        contribute to the Phylo project and help us to make a version of the game in your favorite language.
        </p>
        
        <p>
        <b>Step 1:</b> For conveniencies, the text to be transalated is split in two files. The first one (Main text)
        contains the text used in the game and satellite pages. The second one (Tutorial text) contains the text
        used in the tutorial. We provided these two files in 3 format: Rich Text Format (.rtf), Microsoft Word Document (.docx)
        and OpenDocument (.odt). You can use the format of your choice. 
        
        Download the following file in your favorite format:
        <table>
            <tr>
                <td>Main text:</td><td><a href="docs/GametextforPhylo.rtf">[Rich text format]</a>&nbsp;<a href="docs/GametextforPhylo.docx">[Word]</a>&nbsp;<a href="docs/GametextforPhylo.odt">[OpenDocument]</a></td>
            </tr>
                <td>Tutorial text:</td><td><a href="docs/TutorialtextforPhylo.rtf">[Rich text format]</a>&nbsp;<a href="docs/TutorialtextforPhylo.docx">[Word]</a>&nbsp;<a href="docs/TutorialtextforPhylo.odt">[OpenDocument]</a></td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        </p>
        
        <p>
        <b>Step 2:</b> Translate these two files as indicated in the header of the document.
        </p>
        
        <p>
        <b>Step 3:</b> Indicate the language and your name in the first fields, so that we can credit you on our credits page!
        </p>
        
        <p>
        <b>Step 4:</b> Return your file completed to <a href="mailto:phylo-submit@cs.mcgill.ca?subject=[Phylo] Translation">phylo-submit@cs.mcgill.ca</a>
        </p>
        
        <p>
        N.B.: Phylo has already been translated in 9 languages but translations can always be improved. If you want to improve existing translation please email us at
        <a href="mailto:phylo-info@cs.mcgill.ca?subject=Improving existing translation">phylo-info@cs.mcgill.ca</a> and we will send you the files currently used for any language.
        </p>

              

        
        
